      • setParent

        public void setParent(Entity parent)
        Description copied from interface: Entity
        Updates the parent of this entity.
        This method makes sure that the old and the new parent keep their entities list updated, by automatically calling Entity.addEntity(Entity) and Entity.removeEntity(Entity).

        A CoreNotificationCodes.ENTITY_PARENT_CHANGED notification is thrown.
        Additionally, each descendant of this entity (ie: entities who have this entity as their direct or not direct parent) are notified using CoreNotificationCodes.ENTITY_ANCESTOR_CHANGED.

        Specified by:
        setParent in interface Entity
        Overrides:
        setParent in class EntityImpl

      • getVirtualMachines

        public List<VirtualMachine> getVirtualMachines()
        Description copied from interface: User
        Returns a list of VirtualMachine that are owned by this user.

        The returned virtual machines are not actual children of this User entity, and the list is kept updated indirectly through listening to NotificationCodes.USER_VM_ATTACHED and NotificationCodes.USER_VM_DETACHED.

        The returned list should not include ThinClientVirtualMachines. Use User.getThinClients() to get ThinClients first if you want to list those.

        Specified by:
        getVirtualMachines in interface User
        Returns:
        a list of VirtualMachine that are owned by this user

        public List<StorageFile> getStorageFiles()
